verbose_text: RT-qPCR, western blot analysis and ELISA indicated that succinate exposure upregulated VEGF expression, activated the extracellular signal regulated protein kinase (ERK) 1/2, c-Jun N-terminal kinase (JNK) and p38 mitogen activated protein kinase (MAPK) signaling pathways and led to the release of cyclooxygenase-2 (COX-2) and prostaglandin E 2 (PGE 2).
